<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="416" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Fogg</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 57.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 15, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Upon the receipt of your despatch No. 63,
                            of the 9th ultimo, relative to the proposed exchange of arms between
                            Switzerland and the United States, a letter upon the subject was
                            addressed to the Secretary of War, to which a reply has just been
                            received, of which I herewith enclose a transcript. You will learn from
                            this that the arms and accoutrements for the Swiss government are now
                            nearly ready for transportation.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">George G. Fogg</hi>, Esq, &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>